						               													<description>From the instruction guide:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Introduce an element of play with these fun-to-use Alphabet Dice.  These extra-large sized dice can be useful for stimulating many word and spelling games.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This guide is not intended to be a comprehensive set of notes for the dice, but rather an offering of a variety of games and activities which are sure to generate many more ideas by both you and your students.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The set consists of 12 dice.  Two dice have only vowels printed on the six sides.  The other ten dice have a combination of consonants, vowels and blends printed on the six sides.  The letters are arranged on the die with the more commonly used letters appearing most often.  Following is a chart indicating how often each letter or blend appears in the set.&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;a-4 &amp;#10;b-2 &amp;#10;c-2 &amp;#10;ch-2&amp;#10;ck-2&amp;#10;d-2 &amp;#10;e-6&amp;#10;f-2&amp;#10;g-2&amp;#10;h-2&amp;#10;i-2&amp;#10;j-2&amp;#10;k-2&amp;#10;l-2&amp;#10;m-2&amp;#10;n-3&amp;#10;o-4&amp;#10;p-2&amp;#10;qu-2&amp;#10;r-4&amp;#10;s-2&amp;#10;sh-2&amp;#10;t-2&amp;#10;th-2&amp;#10;u-3&amp;#10;v-2&amp;#10;w-2&amp;#10;x-2&amp;#10;y-2&amp;#10;z-2&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Games suggested in the instructions:&amp;#10;Make A Word (3 to 5 players)&amp;#10;Write A Word (4 to 5 players)&amp;#10;Nonsense Words or Not? (2 players)&amp;#10;What's the Word? (4 to 5 players)&amp;#10;along with other suggested games&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Interesting is the fact that the same letter has different values on different dice.  For example, the letter &amp;quot;a&amp;quot; has a value of 1, on the dice with all vowels (a,e,e,i,o,u) but the same letter &amp;quot;a&amp;quot; has a value of 3, on a mixed die with vowels and consonants (a,l,n,o,p,r).  Also, there are five blends:  ch (worth 5), ck (worth 6), qu (worth 6), sh (worth 5), and th (worth 5).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
